spans.text: Fortune and honours wait the brave
The youth Maria's heart preferred , Resolved to
the main , And far the bounding vessel flies
OH , Henry , they were fixed on thee
glory's pride , nor fiercest war , Maria from his thoughts
absent long , and distant far , She still was nearest to his heart
glory's pride , nor fiercest war , Maria from his thoughts
the time appears in view , When we again in joy
Her thoughts beyond the waters reach , OH , Henry ! she expected thee
the Atlantic's troubled breast , And dire destruction
the water's roar , And death and desolation
in mercy given ; And patience must support the blow Inflicted by the hand of heaven
her seated on the beach , Her eyes were fixed upon the sea , Her thoughts the depths of ocean reach
OH , Henry ! still they followed thee
her eyes The dews of sorrow
Read thy loved name on this white stone
